<br>
That does sound highly counter-productive..<br>
<br>
In the meanwhile I've been working on my funky mech. Here's a snapshot:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.puonti.net/puontimech.jpg">www.puonti.net/puontimech.jpg</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
I'm working on this in Flash (just like the background). The white lines are early sketches, while the more finished areas already have more or less proper shades and shadows. The green line on the right is my &quot;perspective line&quot;. It originates from the right perspective point, and I drag the leftmost end around to check that everything's in perspective. There is another similar line coming from the left perspective point, but it's not shown in this picture.<br>
<br>
The huge hole on the front of the mech is an opening for forward-firing guns (the cavity serves as partial protection for the guns). The &quot;slab&quot; in the middle of the mech is part of the cockpit's entryway - it slides upwards a bit and then the whole top opens enough to allow the operator to enter or leave.<br>
<br>
The red rectangle is obviously the 2 meter guideline for this particular spot. <br>
<br>
